# Pstack execution

Read [AGENTS.md](mdc:AGENTS.md) (workstreams, merge order) and [docs/PSTACK_USAGE.md](mdc:docs/PSTACK_USAGE.md) when starting implementation work.

## Routing

- **Scope first:** `@pm-developer` or the agent brief in AGENTS.md — not `/poteto-mode`.
- **Implement:** `/poteto-mode <task>` for any non-trivial code change, bug fix, perf work, or refactor.
- **Cross-boundary changes:** `/architect` before coding (see [architect.mdc](mdc:.cursor/rules/architect.mdc)).
- **After planning:** use the global `model-recommender` skill for model choice; do not duplicate pstack principle text here.

## Workstream discipline

- Stay in the assigned workstream slice (A / B / C / D / S). See [padel-multi-agent.mdc](mdc:.cursor/rules/padel-multi-agent.mdc).
- Spawn implementation subagents with `subagent_type: "poteto-agent"`, not `generalPurpose`.
- Merge order: shared types → server → client.

## Verification

- UI / overlay: `control-ui` (cursor-team-kit).
- CLI / scripts / CV pipeline: `control-cli` (cursor-team-kit).
- Before commit: `/deslop`.
- After opening a PR: `/babysit`.

## Plugins required

`pstack` and `cursor-team-kit` must be enabled (Cursor Settings → Plugins). Install with `/add-plugin pstack` if missing.
